<div class="col-md-12">
    <p>
        The Main Attraction Of Central Dooars Is Jaldapara Forests. This Is Also The Oldest Tourist Destination Of The Area.
        The Holong Bungalow Inside The Forest Has Seen Many A Tourists Including Vip’s There. Chilapata Is The Adjacent Forest Which Has Gained Prominence In The Recent Past. The Entry Point To Bhutan
        Through Phuentsholing Is Also In This Area.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Central Dooars Jaldapara</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access </b>
    <p>
        The Main Entry Point Is From Madarihat Town, Situated Adjacent To N.H.-31 In Between Hasimara And Birpara. The Nearest Railway Station, Falakata Is 22 Kms From Madarihat.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Largest Population Of Great Indian One Horned Rhinoceros In West Bengal Is Found At Jaldapara. It Also Provides Excellent Habitat For The Royal Bengal Tiger And Other Animals Like Gaur, Leopard, Sambar, Chital, Hog Deer, Barking Deer Etc.
        <br />* Jaldapara W.L.S.. Is Closed During Rainy Season From 16th. June To 15th. Sept.
    </p>
    <b>Circuit Routing</b>
    <p>
        Is Jaldhapara,Suntaley  Khola, Bindu, Jaldhaka, Chapramari, Neora Valley Forms A Circuit Worth Visiting
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-danger">OTHER ATTRACTION IN & AROUND</h4>
    <h4 class="text-info">Chapramari Wildlife Sanctuary </h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Chapramari Sanctuary Is Close To Chalsa Railway Station And Nearly 100 Kilometers From New Jalpaiguri Railway Station / Bagdogra Airport / Siliguri.
        Chapramari Is Close To Gorumara National Park. It Is Situated In The Foothills Of Lesser Himalaya.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        It Is Home To Elephant, One Horned Rhinoceros, Hog Deer, Reptiles, Huge Wild Tuskers, Leopards, Spotted Deer, Sambar, Civet, Wild Boars, Etc. One Horned Rhino Are Breaded Here.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">The Neora Valley</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Neora Valley Sanctuary Stretches From Kalimpong The Subdivision Of Darjeeling In India To Bhutan In The North And Dooars In The South. This Valley Has An Entry Point From Lava In Kalimpong Sub Division And Is A Natural Heritage Forests With Dense Bamboo Groves. 
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Red Panda And A Few Rare Species Of Birds Can Be Spotted Here. The Forest Is Diversified With Dense Colorful Canopy, Orchids, Pine And Many Other Trees. A Trek Of Two To Three Nights Is One Of The Adventures With The Other Adventure Being Bird Watching. The Forest Has A Wide Range Of Avian – Fauna And One Can Spot Migratory Birds In Winters Also. Some Of The Birds Like Pheasants, Mynas, Flycatchers, Parakeets, Partridges, Orioles, Owls, Cuckoos, Minivets, Swifts And Woodpeckers Can Be Spotted Quite Often. Other Interesting Wildlife That Can Be Spotted Are Himalayan Black Bear, Common Leopard, Barking Deer, Gural, Deer, Lesser Cats, Himalayan Thar, Serrow, Indian Gaur And Squirrels Is Worth Spotting. Red Panda Though Shy Can Be Spotted Here By The Lucky Ones.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Bindu / Samsing</h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        Is Close To Chalsa / Malbazar. Bindu, Jhalong, Suntaley Khola Is Under One Circuit And Forms A Days Excursion. They Are Close And One Can Stay At Bindu Or At Chalsa Or Lataguri And Visit This Place. It Is Nearly Three To Four Hours Drive Nearly Hundred Kilometers From Siliguri And Is Approachable By Road Only. The Nearest Railway Station Is Chalsa From Where Its One And Half Hours Drive And The Major Railway Station Is New Jalpaiguri.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        Bindu Is A Small Settlement In The Hills Situated In The Northern Part Of Dooars With Beautiful Scenic Beauty. There Are Quite A Few Places Of Interest Staying At Bindu They Are Jaldhaka, Suntaleykhola, Samsing, Chapramari And The Village Nearby Are Worth Visiting. Going Around This Place Is An Experience By Itself, Visiting The Banks Of River Jaldhaka And Birding Or Angling Is Recommended To Visitors. Bindu Is The Last Hamlet By Road Near The Bhutan Border.
    </p>
    <h4 class="text-info">Suntaleykhola </h4>
    <b>Location, Approach & Access</b>
    <p>
        This Tourist Destination Suntaleykhola Is Situated On The Northern Part Of Dooars And Is A Scenic Place For Tourist To Spend Some Time. . It Is Generally Used As A Day Excursion. Guest Can Visit This Place From Either Of The Nearby Destinations. This Region Forms An Excursion For Tourist Staying In Lataguri, Dhupguri, Chalsa Or Malbazar.
    </p>
    <b>Prime Attraction</b>
    <p>
        The Word Is Made Up Of Two Words Suntaley And Khola. The Literal Meaning Is Orange And Stream Respectively.
        This Place Of Suntaley Khola, Bindu, Jaldhaka, Chapramari, Neora Valley Forms A Circuit. Otherwise It Can Also Be Enjoyed Any Time Of The Year, Specially The Monsoon. Rocky Island Is A Nice Place Nearby For Group And Large Family Outings / Excursions.
    </p>
